Run Setup Guide

1. Create Environment (First Time)
    python3 -m venv .venv

2. Activate the Environment
    source .venv/bin/activate

3. Install Dependencies
    pip install fastapi uvicorn python-dotenv google-adk litellm pymongo streamlit matplotlib pandas

4. Configure Environment (.env)
    Configure the following variables:
      - LOCAL_MODEL_NAME: Main aggregator model (e.g. openai/qwen2.5-coder-7b-instruct-mlx)
      - LOCAL_PARALLEL_MODEL_NAME: Model for parallel sub-agents (e.g. openai/llama-3.2-3b-instruct)
      - OPENAI_API_BASE: Local server port (e.g. http://localhost:1234/v1)
      - OPENAI_API_KEY: lm-studio

5. Start Local LLM Server
    Open LM Studio and start the Local Server on port 1234. Load the models you want to use.
    For local performance optimization, you can run a lightweight model for the parallel extraction sub-agents:
      - Qwen-2.5-1.5B-Instruct / Qwen-2.5-3B-Instruct (highly recommended)
      - Llama-3.2-3B-Instruct / Llama-3.2-1B-Instruct
    Load the models in LM Studio or using the CLI:
      lms load qwen2.5-coder-7b-instruct-mlx
      lms load llama-3.2-3b-instruct

6. Run the FastAPI Backend
    uvicorn main:app --reload

7. Run the Streamlit Frontend
    streamlit run app.py